{"lemma":"عَصَبَةُ","slug":"عَصَبَةُ","root":"ع.ص.ب","root_slug":"ع-ص-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ص-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَصَبَةُ","root":"عصب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29275","n29276","n29277","n29278"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a league (a group or association of cooperating members)","examples":[{"text":"عُصْبَةُ الأُمَم","english":"League of Nations"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a faction (a group of people)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a clique (a small, exclusive group of individuals)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun from عَصَبَ (ʕaṣaba, “to bind”)."},"ipa":["/ʕusˤ.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29275","headword_ar":"عَصْبَةٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobN","text_ar":"عُصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29276","headword_ar":"عُصْبَةٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobN","text_ar":"عُصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company, of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, O, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who league together to defend one another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O; [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabapN","text_ar":"عَصَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in number from ten to forty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, O, Msb;) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"about ten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, Msb:) or accord. to Akh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbapN","text_ar":"عِصَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; having no sing.: (O:) or ↓ the latter, (S, O, Msb,) or each, (K,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assemblage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men, and of horses, (S, O, Msb, K,) or of horses with their riders, (TA,) and of birds, (S, O, Msb, K,) and of other things, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in number from ten to forty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) or the former"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from three to ten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of forty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of seventy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but said to be originally applied to an unlimited number: its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSabN","text_ar":"عُصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth, Msb, TA:) and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbapN","text_ar":"عِصَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAy^ibu","text_ar":"عَصَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, Msb, TA.) It is said in a trad. of 'Alee that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodaAl","text_ar":"اَبْدَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"are in Syria; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nujabaA='","text_ar":"نُجَبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", in Egypt; and the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAy^ib","text_ar":"عَصَايِب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in El-'Irák; meaning, by the last,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Companies assembled for wars:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of devotees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because coupled with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbdAl","text_ar":"ابدال"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"njbA'","text_ar":"نجباء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","S","O","Msb","IF","K","TA","IAth"]},{"entry_id":"n29277","headword_ar":"عِصْبَةٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winding round, one's head"},{"kind":"text","text":"with a turban or the like. (L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29278","headword_ar":"عَصَبَةٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabN","text_ar":"عَصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, &c. [See the latter word in the paragraph headed by it and also voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobN","text_ar":"عُصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  Also A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, who league together for his defence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobapN","text_ar":"عُصْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) thus accord. to the leading lexicologists. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heirs of a man who has left neither parent nor offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [particularly], with respect to the [portions of inheritances termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^iD","text_ar":"فَرَايِض"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyDapN","text_ar":"فَرِيضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all such as have not a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyDap","text_ar":"فَرِيضَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"named, and who receive if there remain anything after"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the distribution of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^iD","text_ar":"فَرَايِض"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) thus accord. to those who treat of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frAy^D","text_ar":"فرايض"},{"kind":"text","text":", and accord. to the [other] lawyers: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations by the side of the males:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is the meaning of what is said by the leading lexicologists: (Msb:) or, as is said by Az, a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heirs consisting of male relations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sons, and relations on the father's side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) so called because they encompass him; the father being a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taraf","text_ar":"طَرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. an extremity in the right line], and so the son, and the paternal uncle being a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. a collateral relation], and so the brother: (Az, S, TA:) or a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations on the father's side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA;) because they encompass him and he is strengthened by them: (TA:) afterwards it became applied to a single person as well as to a pl. number, and both a male and a female: (Mgh:) or the lawyers apply it to a single person when there is no other than he, because he stands in the place of the collective number in receiving the whole of the property; and in the language of the law it is applied to a female in certain cases relating to emancipation and inheritances, but not otherwise either in the proper language or in the language of the law: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSuwbapN","text_ar":"عُصُوبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as its inf. n. [meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of being persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person, to whom the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabapN","text_ar":"عَصَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is applied"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh:) it is said [by Az] in the T, “ I have not heard any sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabapN","text_ar":"عَصَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to analogy it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaASibN","text_ar":"عَاصِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAlibN","text_ar":"طَالِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalabapN","text_ar":"طَلَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” (TA: [and the like is also said in the Mgh: in the Msb it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabapN","text_ar":"عَصَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaASibN","text_ar":"عَاصِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafarapN","text_ar":"كَفَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfirN","text_ar":"كَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabaAtN","text_ar":"عَصَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Msb","S","Az","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}